# TradeSync Pro — Global Rules

## Project Structure
This is a 3-layer copy trading platform:
- trade-sync-backend: NestJS + TypeORM + MSSQL on port 3000
- trade-sync-frontend: Next.js App Router + Tailwind + Redux on port 3001  
- trade-sync-client: Python 3.9+ + PySide6 + MetaTrader5 desktop app

## Source of Truth Files
Before making any change, read:
1. SYSTEM_CONTRACT_MATRIX.md — all REST routes and socket contracts
2. The relevant layer README (backendReadme.md / frontendReadme.md / clientReadme.md)

## Non-Negotiable Rules
- Never rename socket events: register_node, test_signal, trade_execution
- Never remove required payload keys: event, master_ticket, symbol, action, volume
- Never add JWT guards — project intentionally has none
- Never use alert() in frontend — use console.error()
- All changes must be ADDITIVE — no existing routes or DB columns removed
- Update SYSTEM_CONTRACT_MATRIX.md whenever a new route or socket event is added
- Update the relevant layer README for every new file, route, or component

## Code Style
- Python: match existing indentation (4 spaces), use print() with colorama for logs
- TypeScript: no 'any' on new code, match existing service/controller patterns
- React: 'use client' where needed, Tailwind only for styling